$Id: README 531 2005-04-23 04:34:32Z phf $

A basic single-pass compiler for a MINImalistic programming language

Peter Froehlich <phf@acm.org>
http://www.factorial.com/forward/phf/work/

The programming language Mini was designed by Fridtjof Siebert, see
the KUDOS file. This version is written in Python and generates MIPS
code for the SPIM simulator. The language itself is unchanged, all
the original example programs work. :-)

mini.tex
mini.pdf
  Translation of Fridtjof's Mini.LiesMich file

buffer.py
generator.py
mini.py
parser.py
scanner.py
spim.py
version.py
  Python implementation

factorial.mini
fibonacci.mini
gcd.mini
prime.mini
  Fridtjof's original example programs

4711.mini
count.mini
empty.mini
  Some test cases I wrote up, not impressive

grammar.ebnf
  Fridtjof's original grammatik.ebnf

